What:		"l2_drops" trap group
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	A trap group registered by netdevsim which contains packet
		traps for packets that were dropped by the device during
		layer 2 forwarding (i.e., bridge).

What:		"l3_drops" trap group
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	A trap group registered by netdevsim which contains packet
		traps for packets that were dropped by the device or hit an
		exception (e.g., TTL error) during layer 3 forwarding.

What:		"buffer_drops" trap group
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	A trap group registered by netdevsim which contains packet
		traps for packets that were dropped by the device due to
		enqueue decision.

What:		"ingress_smac_mc" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps incoming packets that the device decided to drop because
		of a multicast source MAC.

What:		"ingress_vlan_tag_allow" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps incoming packets that the device decided to drop in case
		the ingress bridge port is not configured with a PVID and the
		packet is untagged or prio-tagged.

What:		"ingress_vlan_filter" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps incoming packets that the device decided to drop in case
		they are tagged with a VLAN that is not configured on the
		ingress bridge port.

What:		"ingress_stp_filter" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps incoming packets that the device decided to drop in case
		the STP state of the ingress bridge port is "listening",
		"disabled" or "blocking".

What:		"empty_tx_list" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps packets that the device decided to drop in case after
		layer 2 forwarding there are no ports to transmit the packet
		through.

What:		"loopback_filter" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps packets that the device decided to drop in case after
		layer 2 forwarding the packet should be transmitted through the
		same port from which it was received.

What:		"blackhole_route" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps packets that the device decided to drop in case they hit
		a "blackhole" route.

What:		"ttl_error" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps unicast packets that should be forwarded by the device
		whose TTL was decremented to 0 or less.

What:		"tail_drop" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps packets that the device decided to drop because they
		could not be enqueued to a transmission queue which is full.

What:		"early_drop" trap
Date:		29-Apr-2019
KernelVersion:	v5.2
Contact:	netdev@vger.kernel.org
Description:	Traps packets that the device decided to drop due to the
		decision of the Random Early Detection (RED) queueing
		discipline to early drop the packet.
